ch.usi.inf.lidr.selection
Class SUSHI.Regression

java.lang.Object
  ch.usi.inf.lidr.selection.SUSHI.Regression
Enclosing class:
SUSHI
private abstract static class SUSHI.Regression
extends Object

An abstract class that performs regression of the type y = a * f(x) + b, where the function f should be overridden by subclasses.

Author:
Ilya Markov

predict

public double predict(double x)
Returns the "predicted" y value associated with the supplied x value, based on the data that has been added to the model so far. In particular, y = a * f(x) + b, where a and b are estimated by the regression.

Returns 0 if the number of added observations is less than 2.

Parameters:
x - The input x value.
Returns:
The predicted y value.

getRSquare

public double getRSquare()
Returns the coefficient of determination usually denoted as r^2.

Returns 0 if the number of added observations is less than 2.

Returns:
Pearson's r.
